texts of the 17th century. The epistemological reconstructions and analyses of source examples present the conceptions of space at the intersections of Chinese scholars' reflections on reality, the universe, human cognition, and linguistic and visual expressive capacities.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Regional Studies.2bisacsh  aPremodern Chinese philosophy and art.  atheory of space.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z97831113181270 cEPUBz97831107919760 cprintz978311079182240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110791860zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110791860zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110791860/original  a978-3-11-131812-7 EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA